  "notes": "Kermani Persian (Kermānī). Southern Iranian; Kerman province. /æ/ → [a] (more open/back than Tehran; similar to Shirazi). /q/ somewhat more maintained than Tehran. Contact with Balochi (southeastern Iran): minor phonological effects. Zoroastrian community in Kerman shares some features with Yazdi.",
